  <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/Sepherenia?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/bottletr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Bards are the best class.</span><hr size=1> Thank you Minute, you hit it right on the button. Geez, I don't know how many ppl I have seen trying to play a bard. It takes time and patience and some serious research to play this class effectively. Lag does take a huge toll on twisting abilities.<br>
<br>
I love being Sepherenia most of the time, but she is NOT easy to play. On nights that my wrists are bothering me, I either look for a group that just mainly wants cantata of replenishment or go play my druid instead. Being a bard at higher lvl's can be frustrating at times, but is part and parcel once again of playing a class that has no one single &quot;the best&quot; at besides running very fast.<br>
<br>
My class is a multi-utility class, and the description I give is that, &quot;I am an armor wearing caster.&quot; I die just as fast as a caster and my hps are like one too. <br>
<br>
Bards played effectively can be a very wicked addition to any group, but on the other hand, a poorly played one just adds to the stereotype that bards are not needed in certain groups. <br>
<br>
/hugs<br>
Sepherenia Crystalwind<br>
